text: Billens-Hennens is a municipality of the district Glâne in the canton of Fribourg in Switzerland. It was created on 1 January 1998 from the former municipalities of Billens (Dictionnaire-Dikchenéro: Français-Patois/Patê- Franché. Société cantonale des patoisans fribourgeois. Fribourg: 2013. p. 77) and Hennens ( or InninDictionnaire-Dikchenéro: Français-Patois/Patê-Franché. Société cantonale des patoisans fribourgeois. Fribourg: 2013. p. 207) merged into the municipality of Billens-Hennens.Amtliches Gemeindeverzeichnis der Schweiz published by the Swiss Federal Statistical Office accessed 19 July 2011 == References == == Other websites == * Official website * * Category:Municipalities in Glâne
